[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA stack-buffer-overflow was detected by AddressSanitizer during a libFuzzer-based [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing session of the Mongoose codebase. The overflow occurs in the formatting [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroutines—specifically within the functions mg_pfn_iobuf_private and [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmg_vxprintf—resulting in a one-byte write just past the end of a stack-allocated [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The issue was triggered by the fuzz target function LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput, which[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfeeds arbitrary data into the HTTP parser [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mg_http_parse`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During parsing, the library attempts to log or format data via `mg_log`, which [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternally calls `mg_vxprintf`.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a write of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at address corresponding to offset [0m[1;36m120[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the `mg_vxprintf` stack frame. This location lies immediately past a local array[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`tmp371`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that occupies bytes [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m112[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m120[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow originates in `mg_pfn_iobuf_private` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `mongoose/src/printf.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich is invoked by `mg_putchar_iobuf_static` → `scpy` → `mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mongoose/src/fmt.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, eventually leading to `mg_snprintf` and related routines.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call stack [0m[1;39m([0m[39mabbreviated[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfuzz target[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `mg_http_parse` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mongoose/src/http.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `mg_log` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mongoose/src/log.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `mg_vxprintf` and `mg_pfn_iobuf_private` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mongoose/src/fmt.c`, [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mongoose/src/printf.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key artifacts and observations:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The vulnerable buffer is declared in `mg_vxprintf` around line [0m[1;36m276[0m[39m of `fmt.c`.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The overflow happens when formatting floating-point or other data via `mg_dtoa`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand friends.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The fuzzer ran with libFuzzer’s entropic power schedule, [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m iterations on the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame input, under an RSS limit and timeout.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- To understand the full impact and context, review:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • All buffer allocations and bounds handling in `mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The I/O buffer functions in `printf.c`, especially `mg_pfn_iobuf_private` and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`scpy`  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • How `mg_log` formats messages and passes them to these routines  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The HTTP parsing logic in `mg_http_parse` that invokes logging and formatting [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mFUZZER[0m[39m=[0m[35mfuzz[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ shift[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/fmt.[0m[1;92mc:275[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m283[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m277[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'g'[0m[39m || c == [0m[32m'f'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m280[0m[39m:          k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, v, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pr, c == [0m[32m'g'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m281[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mis_long == [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m282[0m[39m:          int64_t v = [0m[1;35mva_arg[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*ap, int64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m283[0m[39m:          k = [0m[1;35mmg_lld[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, v, s, h[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack-buffer-overflow arises in the ‘e’[0m[35m/[0m[39m’E’ formatting branch of [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmg_vxprintf [0m[1;39m([0m[39msrc/fmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. That branch declares a fixed `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` but calls [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, allowing up to [0m[1;36m9[0m[39m characters plus a terminator into an [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By contrast, the ‘g’[0m[35m/[0m[39m’f’ branch correctly uses `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` with [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, matching buffer capacity to the dstlen passed to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmg_dtoa.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - mg_dtoa can produce longer strings [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding exponent notation[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m than [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpassing a dstlen larger than the buffer silently overruns the stack.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patching Strategy[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In src/fmt.c, locate the ‘e’[0m[35m/[0m[39m’E’ handling code around line [0m[1;36m318[0m[39m of mg_vxprintf:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'e'[0m[39m || c == [0m[32m'E'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         double d = [0m[1;35mva_arg[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*ap, double[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         int64_t exponent = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mlog10[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mmy_fabs[0m[1;39m([0m[39md[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         double mantissa = d [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35mpower[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, exponent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         n += [0m[1;35mscpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mout, param, tmp, k[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mout[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, param[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Modify this block to mirror the safe pattern used in the ‘g’[0m[35m/[0m[39m’f’ branch:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Increase the local buffer to at least the size used by the `mg_dtoa` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternal buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m40[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Pass the actual buffer size [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as dstlen.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patched code becomes:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'e'[0m[39m || c == [0m[32m'E'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         double d = [0m[1;35mva_arg[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*ap, double[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         int64_t exponent = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mlog10[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mmy_fabs[0m[1;39m([0m[39md[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         double mantissa = d [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35mpower[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, exponent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Ensure dstlen matches tmp’s capacity to prevent overflow *[0m[35m/[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         n += [0m[1;35mscpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mout, param, tmp, k[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mout[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, param[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Functionality[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We retain the exact formatting logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomputing exponent and mantissa, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvoking mg_dtoa, copying via scpy, and emitting the format specifier with [0m[1;35mout[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The only change is increasing the temporary buffer size and aligning dstlen to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe buffer’s true capacity.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We do not touch any harness, tests, or external libraries—only the vulnerable [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msource path in fmt.c.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification and Side-Effect Mitigation[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Matching dstlen to buffer size is a direct compliance with mg_dtoa’s contract [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand mirrors the proven ‘g’[0m[35m/[0m[39m’f’ branch.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte stack allocation per invocation is modest: identical to the f/g [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbranch and unlikely to impact real-world stack usage significantly.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There is no change to code paths outside mg_vxprintf’s ‘e’[0m[35m/[0m[39m’E’ branch, so [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother formatting remains untouched.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This fix closes the one-byte overflow without risking broader regressions.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. References to Similar Code Patterns[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Lines [0m[1;36m275[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m283[0m[39m in fmt.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe ‘g’[0m[35m/[0m[39m’f’ branch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m illustrate the intended usage:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, v, pr, c == [0m[32m'g'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch brings the e/E branch into line with this safe pattern.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWith this patch, mg_vxprintf no longer overruns its stack buffer when formatting in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexponential notation, resolving the AddressSanitizer-detected overflow. [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-          k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+          k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pr, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer–detected stack-buffer-overflow in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmongoose’s formatting code. During fuzzing, a one-byte write just beyond the end of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma local buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp371`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in mg_vxprintf [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is reported, triggered by logging [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin HTTP parsing. The patch attempt enlarged one temporary buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` formatting branch from [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m bytes and updated the mg_dtoa call to pass[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe new buffer size. After applying this change, the same overflow resurfaces at [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same stack location, indicating that the root overflow in mg_vxprintf remains [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munaddressed.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzer invokes LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput → mg_http_parse → mg_log → mg_vxprintf.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a write of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at address just past a stack object [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`tmp371`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the mg_vxprintf frame [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.[0m[1;92mc:247[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow occurs in mg_pfn_iobuf_private [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprintf.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the underlying buffer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow is in fmt.c: a local array covering offsets [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m112[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m120[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is exceeded by a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite at offset [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The call chain includes mg_vsnprintf/mg_snprintf → mg_dtoa → back into [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmg_vxprintf, suggesting one of the dtoa or formatting routines writes too many [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes into a fixed-size stack buffer.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey Observations from the Initial Log  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The faulty frame in mg_vxprintf has two local arrays: one at [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m72[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mone at [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m112[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m120[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp371`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow is on `tmp371`, a mere [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte buffer, overflowed by one byte.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The error consistently reproduces under fuzzing with entropic power scheduling.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In fmt.c around line [0m[1;36m315[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` case[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, changed:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` → `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, [0m[33mc[0m[39m==[0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` → `k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResults After Patch  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The enlargement of the `%e` buffer did not affect `tmp371`, so the same overflow [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecurs.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39msizes, and usage in each formatting branch.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrectly.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code paths around fmt.c lines [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m276[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m315[0m[39m, and [0m[1;36m319[0m[39m to identify other [0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Key observations:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The overflow happens in the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` formatting branch inside [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_vxprintf`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Two buffers are allocated on the stack: `tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m72[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tmp371[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes [0m[1;36m112[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m120[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A write at offset [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe first byte of the redzone after `tmp371`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicates `tmp371` is too small or being mis-indexed.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The crash propagates through `scpy` into the low-level output function.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The patch modifies the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch of `mg_vxprintf` in `src/fmt.c` around [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m315[0m[39m:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```diff[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   -      [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'e'[0m[39m || c == [0m[32m'E'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp0bja_vzb[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue was an AddressSanitizer–detected stack-buffer-overflow in the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMongoose codebase, triggered during fuzzer-driven execution of `mg_http_parse`. The[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow originates in `mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when formatting floating‐point values,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflowing a fixed-size stack buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp371`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was applied in `src/fmt.c` under the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` formatting branch, replacing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma small [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte buffer with a larger [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-byte mantissa buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp2`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexponent buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`expbuf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, plus formatting logic for sign and padding. [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter re-running the fuzzer with the patch, the same stack-buffer-overflow failure [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreappeared at the identical stack location and frame [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mg_vxprintf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe underlying overflow in that function was not fully addressed.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer invoked `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`, which calls into `mg_http_parse`.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During parsing, `mg_log` uses `mg_vsnprintf` → `mg_vxprintf` to format log [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmessages.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte write overflow at a stack address in the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_vxprintf` frame.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack frame layout shows two local buffers:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffsets [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m72[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `char tmp371[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffsets [0m[1;36m112[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m120[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow write occurs at offset [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m, immediately past `tmp371`’s end, in the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode path handling `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m315[0m[39m in fmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey observations from the ASan log:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Overflow in `mg_pfn_iobuf_private` via `scpy`, called from `mg_vxprintf`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The write address is in the right redzone of `tmp371`, indicating an [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds access by one byte.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The stack region around the overflow shows redzone bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`f3`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m immediately [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter `tmp371`.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLocation: `src/fmt.c`, in the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` handling block starting at original line [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m315[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mChanges include:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Remove `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Cap default precision `pr` at [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m if unset.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Allocate a larger mantissa buffer: `char tmp2[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m64[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Call `[0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp2, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, mantissa, pr, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and copy it.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Output the exponent marker via `[0m[1;35mout[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, param[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. Build an exponent string in `char expbuf[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Sign character  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Ensure at least two digits [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpad with leading zero[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Convert each digit  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m. Copy `expbuf` via `scpy`.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter patch, the code around fmt.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`%e` branch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m looks roughly like:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39melse if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'e'[0m[39m || c == [0m[32m'E'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpr == ~0U[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pr = [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    int64_t exponent = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mlog10[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mfabs[0m[1;39m([0m[39md[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    double mantissa = d [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35mpower[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, exponent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* format mantissa *[0m[35m/[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    char tmp2[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m64[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp2, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpr, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    n += [0m[1;35mscpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mout, param, tmp2, k[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* exponent marker *[0m[35m/[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mout[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, param[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; n++;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* format exponent *[0m[35m/[0m                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < dig; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* copy exponent string *[0m[35m/[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    n += [0m[1;35mscpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mout, param, expbuf, expidx[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Re-running the fuzzer yields the same ASan error:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Stack-buffer-overflow at offset [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m in `mg_vxprintf`  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The overflow is again in the small buffer region labelled `tmp371` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m319[0m[39m in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The crash stack trace is identical, indicating the overflow site was not [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimpacted by the patch.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo fully understand and address the overflows, the following parts of the codebase [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be reviewed:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **mg_vxprintf [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Definition and sizing of all local buffers [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp`, `tmp371`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Handling of format specifiers beyond `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` that may write into these [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffers.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **mg_dtoa and related utility functions [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Behavior when formatting numbers with large precision or wide exponents.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **scpy and mg_pfn_iobuf_private [0m[35m/[0m[39m mg_putchar_iobuf_static [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.c & printf.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**  [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Notes[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msingle patch attempt.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Try different approaches to resolve the issues.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Analysis [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Analysis Report[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Relevant Code Snippets[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_snippets>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/fmt.[0m[1;92mc:317[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m326[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m317[0m[39m:      [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'e'[0m[39m || c == [0m[32m'E'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m318[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m  char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m319[0m[39m:          double d = [0m[1;35mva_arg[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*ap, double[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m320[0m[39m:          int64_t exponent = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mlog10[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mmy_fabs[0m[1;39m([0m[39md[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m321[0m[39m:          double mantissa = d [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35mpower[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, exponent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m322[0m[39m:          k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m323[0m[39m:          n += [0m[1;35mscpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mout, param, tmp, k[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m324[0m[39m:          [0m[1;35mout[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, param[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m325[0m[39m:          n++;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m326[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m  k = [0m[1;35mmg_lld[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, exponent, [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The root cause is the tiny, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte local buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m allocated inside[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch of `mg_vxprintf`.  Both the mantissa [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia `mg_dtoa`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexponent [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia `mg_lld`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can easily exceed [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes, leading to the one‐byte stack [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow detected by ASan.  Although a previous patch introduced larger buffers [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`tmp2[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m64[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, `expbuf[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, it neither removed the original [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte buffer nor [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreused the existing [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte `tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdeclared at the beginning of `mg_vxprintf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mso the overflow persisted.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. High-Level Fix  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   We will remove the small `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` entirely and reuse the already declared [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` for both the mantissa and exponent.  This guarantees a minimum [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes of stack space [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmantissa and exponent strings are each far smaller than [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes in practice[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  Additionally, we clamp the default precision [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pr`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the `%f`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%g` paths[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and implement explicit two‐digit zero‐padding for the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexponent per the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` spec.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Steps  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `src/fmt.c`, locate the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch in `mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m317[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Remove the line `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` so no small buffer is allocated.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Immediately after reading the argument `double d = [0m[1;35mva_arg[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*ap, double[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madd:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpr == ~0U[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pr = [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      to mirror the `%f`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%g` default precision.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Change the call[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      to[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpr, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      so the full [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte buffer is used and precision can’t overflow it.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. After copying the mantissa, emit the exponent marker [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mout[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, param[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincrement `n`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   f. Format the exponent with zero‐padding to at least two digits by:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Outputting `[0m[32m'+'[0m[39m` or `[0m[32m'-'[0m[39m` via `[0m[1;35mout[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If the absolute exponent is `< [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m`, output a leading `[0m[32m'0'[0m[39m`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Converting the absolute exponent to a string via `[0m[1;35mmg_lld[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, abs_exp, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfalse, false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` into the [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte `tmp`.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Copying that string via `scpy`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   g. Remove any residual references to `tmp2`, `expbuf`, or other small buffers in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis block.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We still compute `exponent` and `mantissa` the same way.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We preserve default‐precision behavior [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pr = [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We maintain the `[0m[1;35mout[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, param[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call to emit `[0m[32m'e'[0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[32m'E'[0m[39m`.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We continue to use `mg_dtoa` and `mg_lld`, but on a safe [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte buffer.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other formatting paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `%f`, `%g`, integer, string, width/padding [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are untouched.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigations  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` width and padding flags remain minimally supported [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe existing [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode does not fully honor field width for the exponent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  This behavior existed [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore and is unchanged.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Zero‐padding of the exponent to two digits aligns with the standard `%e` spec;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlarger exponents [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., three-digit exponents like `e+[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m still print correctly [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mno truncation[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We reuse the single [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte `tmp` buffer, reducing stack pressure compared to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtwo separate buffers [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp2[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m64[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, `expbuf[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and eliminating potential [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshadowing/ordering issues.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. References in Codebase  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `%f`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%g` branch above already uses `[0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte `tmp`.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Reusing the same buffer here matches that proven, buffer-safe approach.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. No Changes to Harness or Tests  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All edits happen in `src/fmt.c` within `mg_vxprintf`.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzz harnesses, log calls, and other code remain untouched, preserving [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting tests and fuzzing inputs.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
