[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run on the Mongoose HTTP library triggered an AddressSanitizer [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“stack-buffer-overflow” in the formatting code [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mg_vxprintf` → [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_pfn_iobuf_private`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The fuzzer exercised the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` path, overflowing a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msmall temporary buffer on the stack. A patch attempt in `src/fmt.c` removed a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnarrow `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, switched to using an existing `tmp` array with `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor the mantissa, and added manual exponent formatting [0m[1;39m([0m[39msign, zero‐padding to at [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleast two digits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. After rebuilding with the patch, the same ASan error recurred at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same location, indicating the overflow was not addressed.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Running `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` on Mongoose’ HTTP parser led to an [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer report of a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte stack-buffer-overflow in `mg_pfn_iobuf_private`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mcalled from `scpy`, inside `mg_vxprintf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow occurred while handling an `e` or `E` format specifier in [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfile `src/fmt.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, writing past the end of a local buffer on the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The ASan stack trace shows two arrays in the `mg_vxprintf` frame:  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `tmp` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m72[0m[39m, size [0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `tmp371` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes [0m[1;36m112[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m120[0m[39m, size [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The write at offset [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m falls just beyond the end of `tmp371`.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/fmt.c`, the branch handling `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` was modified:  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. The narrow `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` declaration was removed.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `mg_dtoa` was called with `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to write the mantissa into the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting `tmp` buffer.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. A manual exponent formatter was added, composing a sign followed by at least [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtwo digits, and writing that into `tmp` as well.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch did not change the declaration or size of any stack array; it simply [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mswitched buffer usage and logic within the `%e` path.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResult after patch  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A new fuzzing run produced the same ASan crash:  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Location: `mg_pfn_iobuf_private` in `printf.c`, invoked via `scpy` in [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_vxprintf`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Buffer overflow at the same stack offset [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m, again overrunning the [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobject [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp371`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash stack trace and shadow-byte report are identical in form, confirming [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same stack slot is being overrun.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for further investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The definitions and sizes of the local temporary arrays in `mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mboth [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tmp` and `tmp371`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code paths that format floating-point exponents [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mg_dtoa`, the manual [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexponent logic, and any calls to `mg_lld`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The interplay between precision [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pr`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, buffer sizes, and the maximum possible [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexponent width, to determine safe upper bounds.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any other format specifiers in `mg_vxprintf` that use similar temporary buffers [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand could be at risk of overflow.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/fmt.[0m[1;92mc:207[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m215[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m:static size_t [0m[1;35mmg_lld[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar *buf, int64_t val, bool is_signed, bool is_hex[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m208[0m[39m:  const char *letters = [0m[32m"0123456789abcdef"[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m209[0m[39m:  uint64_t v = [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m val;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m210[0m[39m:  size_t s = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, n, i;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m211[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mis_signed && val < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'-'[0m[39m, v = [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m-val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m212[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m This loop prints a number in reverse order. I guess this is because we[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m write numbers from right to left: least significant digit comes last.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Maybe because we use Arabic numbers, and Arabs write RTL?[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mis_hex[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter reviewing the evaluation report, the last patch, and the floating-point [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformatter implementation in `src/fmt.c`, the root cause is clear: the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbranch was using a narrow, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte stack buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, then misusing it [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith two unbounded writers—`[0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…, [0m[33mdstlen[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mmg_lld[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`—causing an [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds write into the redzone of that [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m‐byte buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mASan’s `tmp371`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted patch removed the local `tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, but ASan still reports two buffers in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe stack frame [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte and [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, meaning the [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte buffer in another scope [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains, or the compiler inlined another small buffer, so the overflow persists.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWe need a single, sufficiently large, fixed‐size temporary buffer for the entire [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch—just like the `%f`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%g` code uses the [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte `tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`—and we [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmust guard every write into it by passing the correct length, and ensure the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minteger exponent formatting also respects this capacity. In addition, we must [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure sign, mantissa, decimal point, fractional digits and exponent [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmarker + sign[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ at least two decimal digits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m all fit.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mProposed strategy:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Reintroduce a single, large temporary buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreuse existing `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclared at the top of `mg_vxprintf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove *all* other `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[33m...[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` declarations in inner scopes.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure that the only `tmp` in scope is the outer `tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch, replace the current calls:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Call `[0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpr, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, exactly as in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`%f`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%g`, so the mantissa part never overruns the [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m bytes.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After writing the mantissa, append the exponent marker [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[39m ? [0m[32m'e'[0m[39m : [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m'E'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the exponent sign, and at least two digits of absolute exponent [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalue—building these characters directly at the tail of the mantissa string, taking[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcare to not exceed `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Implement exponent formatting with explicit bounds checking:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After `mg_dtoa` returns `k` bytes of mantissa in `tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m..k-[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, compute [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremaining space `rem = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - k`.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We need at most [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmarker[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39msign[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35mmax_digits[0m[1;39m([0m[39mexponent, unbounded[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcharacters; safe upper bound for IEEE-[0m[1;36m754[0m[39m double is [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m digits for exponent [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrange [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m–[0m[1;36m308[0m[39m to +[0m[1;36m308[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so max [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m decimal digits. Reserve [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m+[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m+[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m = [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes. Even if `pr` is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlarge, exponent is limited by `log10`, so digits ≤ [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor ±[0m[1;36m308[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. To be safe reserve[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes. [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte buffer is ample.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If `rem` is less than that reserved value, clamp or skip, but since [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m==[0m[1;36m40[0m[39m`, this will never happen. Still, we should assert or check: if [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rem < [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, treat as error/unformatted.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Append manually:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mk++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;`  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m marker[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mk++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = exponent < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m ? [0m[32m'-'[0m[39m : [0m[32m'+'[0m[39m;`[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compute `abs_exp = [0m[1;35mllabs[0m[1;39m([0m[39mexponent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compute `digit_count = [0m[1;35mmax[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mfloor[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlog10[0m[1;39m([0m[39mabs_exp[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - For `i = digit_count - [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m … [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`, fill `tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mk + i[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m + [0m[1;39m([0m[39mabs_exp % [0m[1;36m10[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, then [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`abs_exp [0m[35m/[0m[39m= [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m;`[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Update `k += digit_count;`[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Finally, call `n += [0m[1;35mscpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mout, param, tmp, k[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Remove all uses of `mg_lld` or any second `scpy` in the `%e` branch; everything [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmust land inside `tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` with a single `scpy`.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Verify no other small buffers exist in `mg_vxprintf`.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Build and re-run libFuzzer + ASan; confirm no stack‐buffer‐overflow at that [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msite.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This approach preserves existing logic: calls `mg_dtoa` exactly as for `%f`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%g`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthen appends exponent information in a controlled way, in one buffer, respecting [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- We avoid modifying external libs or harness code.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- We preserve full floating-point formatting with default precision, custom [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprecision [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pr`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and uppercase/lowercase markers.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte buffer is proven to be safe for typical DTOA outputs.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By removing `mg_lld` usage here and doing our own bounded loop, we avoid any [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhidden writer that doesn’t respect buffer size.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Downsides: slightly larger code in `%e` branch, but no functional regression. [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTests of `%f`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%g` paths remain untouched. No harness changes needed.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImplementation steps:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. In `src/fmt.c`, locate `mg_vxprintf`.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Confirm top of function has `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`. If not, add it.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. In the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m317[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m327[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Remove any `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` or similar.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. After computing `double d, exponent, mantissa`, call:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      `k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpr, [0m[33mc[0m[39m==[0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Compute `size_t rem = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > k ? [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - k : [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Assert or guard `rem >= [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwe only need up to [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35m1[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmarker[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m+[0m[1;35m1[0m[1;39m([0m[39msign[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m+[0m[1;35m3[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdigits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m5[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. Append marker `tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mk++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;`[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      Append sign `tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mk++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexponent<[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m?[0m[32m'-'[0m[39m:[0m[32m'+'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   f. `unsigned long long abs_e = [0m[1;35mllabs[0m[1;39m([0m[39mexponent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      `int digits = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      `unsigned long long t = abs_e; do [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m digits++; t/=[0m[1;36m10[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m[1;35mwhile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mt>[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      `digits = [0m[1;35mmax[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, digits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      `unsigned long long divisor = [0m[1;35mpow10[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdigits - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      `for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < digits; i++, k++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mk[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m + [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mabs_e [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdivisor[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m % [0m[1;36m10[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; divisor [0m[35m/[0m[39m= [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   g. `n += [0m[1;35mscpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mout, param, tmp, k[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Remove any later second call to `scpy` or `mg_lld` in this branch.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Recompile and test.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis ensures the entire exponential notation fits safely in a single [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte buffer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout overflow.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
